The paper deals with deep neural network pruning and adversarial training, which are both topics that fall under the umbrella of machine learning. Specifically, the paper explores the intersection of sparsity and robustness in neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the potential security risks associated with adversarial examples, which could place it in the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses empirical evaluation and analysis to test the Lottery Ticket Hypothesis, which could place it in the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
